      "review_summary": "The PR adds a best-effort `reader.releaseLock()` after canceling the cloned stream reader in `classifyOpenAISdkStreamBody` and adds a standalone Web Streams lock proof script.\n\nPR surface: Source +3, Tests +63. Total +66 across 2 files.\n\nReproducibility: yes. for the low-level cause: current main cancels the classifier reader without releasing it, and a Node Web Streams probe shows cancel leaves the stream locked until `releaseLock()`. I did not establish an end-to-end OpenClaw provider failure from this exact cleanup gap.",
